cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with developing and evaluating pupil detection algorithms using high-speed eye region videos.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of head-mounted eye trackers in everyday locations and the dataset includes participants wearing glasses, contact lenses, and make-up.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with video data and its analysis.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper benchmarks state-of-the-art pupil detection algorithms on the dataset.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the influence of image resolution and recording location on pupil detection performance.
